dismissalComment.html: Too cute for his own comfort. Tamim tries to scoop-paddle a length-delivery on the leg side, misses. His back feet is dragged out of the crease and McCullum takes out the bails. Was he in, was he out? They refer it to upstairs and verdict is out.

dismissalComment.html: Got 'em. Aftab tries to shift gears but can't get the timing. Good length ball on off, lofted drive but gets under the ball. Manages elevation but no distance. commentTextItems.html: Marshall finishes the game off with a biggie. Down he went on his knee and disposed a flighted delivery over deep midwicket.

commentPostTextItems.html: Another professional performance from New Zealand. Another win. Two more points in the kitty. Six in total. Tough opposition awaits them though. Australia, Sri Lanka and South Africa. Hopefully.... we will get to see some tough contests.

commentTextItems.html: Fleming gets his eight ODI hundred. Also reaches 1000 runs in World Cup games. Take a bow Stephen Fleming. Full, on the middle and leg, he went down on a bent knee and slog-swept it to long leg.
moves to 96 with a thrash to widish long on. one hit away from the landmark
Fleming is peppering the cow corner. Tossed up outside off and he slog swept it, high in the air, in that region between deep midwicket and long on
flat and on the leg and middle, bunted past square-leg
slips down the leg side. He pushed that one through quicker and lost control in the process
short and outside off, cut straight to point
will retain the strike with a push towards square-leg

slightly short in length, Fleming opens the bat-face and late cuts to short third man. Another quick single.
arm-ball, on the off stump, Marshall backs away, the ball hastens towards the off stump and he brings his bat down in time and dabs it to right of short third man

full and on the middle and leg stump line, driven to right of long on. Fleming on strike.

recentReportStory.credit: Siddhartha Vaidyanathan is staff writer of Cricinfo
